<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-12T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-12T15:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00 Colima/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-12T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>147. Reference telegram June 11, noon, from Consulate at Manzanillo,
                            regarding revolutionary disturbances. Department assumes you will make
                            suitable representations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>